marc21:datafield.marc21:subfield: Walt Kuhn scrapbook of press clippings documenting the Armory Show, vol. 1

Scrapbook is primarily filled with newspaper clippings of articles reacting to the exhibition. A few articles pertain to Gutzon Borglum's public resignation from the Association of American Painters and Sculptors.
At the end of the scrapbook are materials pertaining to the exhibit catalog; a sample cover for the "catalogue de-luxe," and an original typescript of the preface by Frederick James Gregg; as well as a poster for the show, with handwritten annotation: official poster of the exhibition, planned by Walt Kuhn, color arrangement by Arthur B. Davies, lettering by Chas. Farrand.
Written on front cover: Press, vol. I.
Cover also has the emblem of the Armory Show (an uprooted pine tree) drawn on.
Vol. 2 has also been scaned, as item 14643. This item should be viewed with item 14643.
Walt Kuhn, Kuhn family papers, and Armory Show records
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
